1) Before you run the file make sure you have installed following library in your workspace or environment.


pip install opencv-python
pip install matplotlib
pip install seaborn


2) Select any image of your choice and name it 'image' and make sure to keep image and jupyter file in same folder.

3) If your image format other than png, (ex:jpeg) is different then change it in program (cell-2). Line is given below.

   "img = cv2.imread("image.png")"
